# Runner keys directive behavior

## Sends literal text and named keys to active pane

The runner should send text keys literally, then named keys like `enter`, to the current active
pane.

    :bins cat python3 scripts/tmcap

> [!NOTE]
> 'cat', 'python3', and 'scripts/tmcap' are available.

    :t new-window -d -n keys 'tmcap keys' (success)
    :p 0:keys.0

    :t wait-for ready-keys (success)
    :k "hello" space "world" enter C-d

    :t wait-for done-keys (success)
    :$ cat keys.txt (exit: 0)

```stdout
hello world
```

## Pane switching sends keys to selected pane

Switching active pane should route keys into the newly selected pane.

    :t new-window -d -n new 'tmcap new' (success)
    :p 0:new.0

    :t wait-for ready-new (success)
    :k "pane-b" enter C-d

    :t wait-for done-new (success)
    :$ cat new.txt (exit: 0)

```stdout
pane-b
```

## Sends hello world as one literal text key

The runner should send a whole phrase as one literal text payload when quoted as a single token.

    :t new-window -d -n text 'tmcap text' (success)
    :p 0:text.0

    :t wait-for ready-text (success)
    :k "hello world" enter C-d

    :t wait-for done-text (success)
    :$ cat text.txt (exit: 0)

```stdout
hello world
```

## Sends punctuation and capitals as literal text

Literal text keys should preserve case and punctuation.

    :t new-window -d -n pct 'tmcap pct' (success)
    :p 0:pct.0

    :t wait-for ready-pct (success)
    :k "Hello, world!" enter C-d

    :t wait-for done-pct (success)
    :$ cat pct.txt (exit: 0)

```stdout
Hello, world!
```

## Sends complex modifier combinations

Complex modifier combinations should be forwarded to tmux as key codes, including explicit
`btab`.

    :t new-window -d -n mod 'tmcap mod' (success)
    :p 0:mod.0

    :t wait-for ready-mod (success)
    :k C-a M-a C-M-a btab C-btab S-up enter C-d

    :t wait-for done-mod (success)
    :$ cat mod.txt (exit: 0)

```stdout
\x01\x1ba\x1b\x01\x1b[Z\x1b[1;2A
```

## Failed pane selection does not retarget active pane

If `:pane` fails, key input should still go to the last successfully selected pane.

    :t new-window -d -n c 'tmcap c' (success)
    :p 0:c.0

    :pane does-not-exist

> [!WARNING]
> No such pane.

    :t wait-for ready-c (success)
    :k "still-c" enter C-d

    :t wait-for done-c (success)
    :$ cat c.txt (exit: 0)

```stdout
still-c
```

